[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "1"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "S:754.AQ875.963.84 J96.J92.QJT.T932 AQ3.63.AK54.AQ65 KT82.KT4.872.KJ7"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
pass pass 1D pass 1H pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 1, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "1eb3e32ce0dfd94173a6fac9a006f33303a53474b52a35e0c7271da465063b8b"]
[Category "Declarer Play"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "declarer_play/suit_establishment"]
[Student "S"]
{North is to play 3NT. East leads the \S2. West puts on the \SJ.

Winners:   \S=2  \H=1  \D=2  \C=1  Total = 6

You need three more winners. It is possible your fourth \D can be established, but that needs a 3-3 split. It's also possible that the \C finesse will work, and also the \H finesse. Since you need the \H finesse anyway you should go ahead and try to establish the \Hs. 

Win the first trick with your \SQ and play a low \H, ducking in dummy. West will no doubt win a cheap trick but no matter. When you next gain the lead play your other low \H and finesse the \HQ. Assume this wins (if it doesn't you will be going down for sure). Play the \HA and if both defenders follow your other 2 \Hs are good and your contract is made.

Ducking the first \H and finessing the second could let you wind up with no tricks at all in the \H suit.

But, it is your only chance to make the contract.}
[Play "W"]S2

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
